{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-article-js","path":"/articles/customizing-locale/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Free Help Center","texts":{"writtenByText":"Written by","allCollectionsText":"All Collections","lastModifiedText":"Last edited","publishedOnText":"Published on"},"language":"en"}},"article":{"id":"047b4092-3f53-580b-8f56-b04ab4795f22","excerpt":"The help center is made to be used in any (left-to-right) language. At the moment only one language can be used at a time. It’s not yet supported to supply…","html":"<p>The help center is made to be used in any (left-to-right) language.</p>\n<p><em>At the moment only one language can be used at a time. It’s not yet supported to supply different languages at the same time</em></p>\n<h3>How to change the language</h3>\n<p>First, you’ll need to open <code class=\"language-text\">gatsby-config.js</code>. There you’ll find a <code class=\"language-text\">siteMetadata</code> section. In there, edit <code class=\"language-text\">language</code> and set it to the two-letter <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_ISO_639-1_codes\">ISO 639-1</a> language code of your desired language.</p>\n<p>This will set the language for SEO purposes (it will apply that language to <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;html lang=&quot;your-language&quot;&gt;</code>)</p>\n<h3>Translating strings</h3>\n<p>Next, you’ll need to translate the default strings inside <code class=\"language-text\">siteMetadata.texts</code> in the same <code class=\"language-text\">gatsby-config.js</code> file.</p>\n<h3>Customize your help center</h3>\n<p>Now that you know about locale, you can continue to learn how to customize your help center in any of these articles:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/articles/customizing-brand-logo\">Adding your own logo</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/articles/customizing-icons\">Working with icons</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/articles/customizing-theme\">Changing the theme</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Or you can go straight to <a href=\"/articles/deploy\">Deploying the Help Center</a>.</p>","fields":{"section":{"id":"customizing","title":"Customizing"},"collection":{"id":"usage","title":"Usage","fields":{"slug":"/collections/usage"}}},"frontmatter":{"title":"Changing the language","date":"2020-01-03T00:00:00.000Z","modifiedDate":null,"description":"Ditch english for something else?","author":{"id":"dferber","name":"Dominik","avatar":{"childImageSharp":{"fixed":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","width":100,"height":100,"src":"/static/d29a0631f9202aa76253afe2ca34750e/71eb7/dferber.png","srcSet":"/static/d29a0631f9202aa76253afe2ca34750e/71eb7/dferber.png 1x,\n/static/d29a0631f9202aa76253afe2ca34750e/92ab1/dferber.png 1.5x,\n/static/d29a0631f9202aa76253afe2ca34750e/b3a76/dferber.png 2x"}}}}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/articles/customizing-locale/"}},"staticQueryHashes":["2584066095","694178885"]}